games.comment: Emmanuel Sanders (5-41, TD) made some nice plays in relief, but was guilty of far too many mistakes (poor route running, drops).

Emmanuel Sanders (2-16). Thomas was quiet for most of the contest, but he exploded in the 4.h quarter and was a key factor on the Broncos' final touchdown drive. As long as the Broncos lack a quality starting quarterback, Thomas is no more than a WR2 at best. Meanwhile, Sanders saw 8 targets, but he wasn't able to do much with them, totaling only the 16 yards. He should bounce back in the near future. Elsewhere,
